# Tools workspace core

**zerwiz/setup is the main repo for tools.** Work there. Do not push tools to WhyNotProductionsHomepage.

## Changelog and commits

- **Changelog path:** `doc/CHANGELOG.md` (in zerwiz/setup)
- **Commit style:** `feat: ...`, `fix: ...`, `docs: ...`, `chore: ...`
- No merge to `main` without a CHANGELOG entry when the change is user- or deploy-relevant.

## Deployment

- **Tools delivery:** zerwiz/setup. Push directly to zerwiz/setup.
- **Curl URLs:** All must point to raw.githubusercontent.com/zerwiz/setup only.
- WhyNotProductionsHomepage is for the homepage only; tools are never pushed there.

## Documentation

- All tool docs live in **`doc/`** (doc/ai-dev-suite/, doc/rag/, etc.).
- Each tool dir keeps a brief README pointing to `doc/<name>/`.
- **When changing a tool:** Update the relevant doc. Add docs (e.g. STORAGE.md, FUNCTIONS.md) when adding features.

